sTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531615\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 06, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rio1665702778587.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rio1665702778587.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rio1665702778587.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rio1665702778587\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                        \n Migration of Counters\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702778587__p_d69056e1_d69057e1_d69058e1\">In Uniface 9, you could define runtime counters in a <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Define Counter</span> dialog as if they were development object definitions that could be compiled into runtime objects. In reality, this dialog wrote the counter name and initial value into the UOBJ.TEXT table, a runtime table.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702778587__p_d69059e1_d69060e1_d69061e1\">In Uniface 10, counters are treated as what they are—runtime data that can only be set and read in ProcScript using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">numgen</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">numset</span>. The counter and initial value can no longer be set in a dialog.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702778587__p_d69062e1_d69063e1_d69064e1\">To migrate counters from Uniface 9 to Uniface 10:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rio1665702778587__li_d31523e1_d31524e1_d31525e1\">If you already initialized counter data using your own logic using <code class=\"ph codeph\">numgen</code>and <code class=\"ph codeph\">numset</code>, you do not have to do anything—that will continue to work.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rio1665702778587__li_d31526e1_d31527e1_d31528e1\">If you used the Define Counter dialog to define and initialize counter data for the application distribution or installation process, you need to:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rio1665702778587__li_d31529e1_d31530e1_d31531e1\">Implement the initialization step using ProcScript instructions.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rio1665702778587__li_d31532e1_d31533e1_d31534e1\">Ensure that UOBJ.TEXT table is properly distributed and installed to ensure that the initial counter data is available.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kez1665702737615.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>UOBJ.TEXT</a><p>The UOBJ.TEXT entity stores runtime counters that can be addressed using the numgen and numset ProcScript statements. The associated table is usually created at runtime.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nlv1665703005447.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>numgen</a><p>Increment the value of the specified counter.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mbq1665703005578.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>numset</a><p>Initialize the value of the specified counter.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531615\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531615\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Migration of Counters Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 06, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Migration of Counters In Uniface 9, you could define runtime counters in a Define Counter dialog as if they were development object definitions that could be compiled into runtime objects. In reality, this dialog wrote the counter name and initial value into the UOBJ.TEXT table, a runtime table. In Uniface 10, counters are treated as what they are—runtime data that can only be set and read in ProcScript using numgen and numset . The counter and initial value can no longer be set in a dialog. To migrate counters from Uniface 9 to Uniface 10: If you already initialized counter data using your own logic using numgen and numset , you do not have to do anything—that will continue to work. If you used the Define Counter dialog to define and initialize counter data for the application distribution or installation process, you need to: Implement the initialization step using ProcScript instructions. Ensure that UOBJ.TEXT table is properly distributed and installed to ensure that the initial counter data is available. Related Links UOBJ.TEXT The UOBJ.TEXT entity stores runtime counters that can be addressed using the numgen and numset ProcScript statements. The associated table is usually created at runtime. numgen Increment the value of the specified counter. numset Initialize the value of the specified counter. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}